{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/96496", "id": 921256143, "node_id": "PR_kwDOAAsO6M426UDP", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/96496", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/96496.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/96496.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96496", "number": 96496, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Implement RFC-2011 (Nicer `assert!` messages)", "user": {"login": "c410-f3r", "id": 17877264, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODc3MjY0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17877264?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r", "html_url": "https://github.com/c410-f3r", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/c410-f3r/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Based on https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/48973\r\nCC https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/44838\r\n\r\n## Functionality\r\n\r\nThe intention here is to show the contents of variables that are outside the declaration of `assert!( ... )`.\r\n\r\n#### Current behavior\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let a = 1;\r\n    let b = true;\r\n    assert!(a == 1 && !b);\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Output:\r\n//\r\n// assertion failed: a == 1 && !b\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### New behavior with this PR\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(generic_assert)]\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let a = 1;\r\n    let b = true;\r\n    assert!(a == 1 && !b);\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Output:\r\n//\r\n// Assertion failed: a == 1 && !b\r\n// With captures:\r\n//  a = 1\r\n//  b = true\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Internals\r\n\r\nAll external `assert!` variables are replaced by a block that tries to copy the intended value and then use this possibly copied element to print useful messages **if** a branch occurs.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    #[derive(PartialEq)]\r\n    struct NoDebug(i32);\r\n    \r\n    let no_debug = NoDebug(1);\r\n    let number = 3i32;\r\n    \r\n    assert!(no_debug != NoDebug(2) && 1 == number);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith this reasoning in mind, the above `assert!` will more or less expand to the following code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[derive(PartialEq)]\r\nstruct NoDebug(i32);\r\n\r\nlet no_debug = NoDebug(1);\r\nlet number = 3i32;\r\n\r\n{\r\n    let mut __capture0 = Capture::new();\r\n    let mut __capture1 = Capture::new();\r\n\r\n    let __local_bind0 = &no_debug;\r\n    let __local_bind1 = &number;\r\n\r\n    if !(\r\n        // no_debug != NoDebug(2)\r\n        *{\r\n            (&Wrapper(__local_bind0)).try_capture(&mut __capture1);\r\n            __local_bind0\r\n        } != NoDebug(2)\r\n        // 1 == number\r\n        && 1 == *{\r\n            (&Wrapper(__local_bind1)).try_capture(&mut __capture2);\r\n            __local_bind1\r\n        }\r\n    ) {\r\n        panic!(\r\n            \"Assertion failed: no_debug != NoDebug(2) && 1 == number\\nWith captures:\\n  no_debug = {:?}\\n  number = {:?}\",\r\n            __capture0,\r\n            __capture1,\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe compiler \"side\" outputs the necessary machinery to make the library \"side\"  decide how an element `T` will or will not be printed.\r\n\r\n## Performance\r\n\r\nIt is inevitable that more instructions will be issued but probably nothing that will have a huge negative impact. Nevertheless, it is possible to optimize certain scenarios to reduce codegen.\r\n\r\n```asm\r\n; https://godbolt.org/z/94rE4dE4a (worst-case)\r\nexample::with_generic_assert:\r\n        sub     rsp, 104\r\n        mov     dword ptr [rsp + 16], 0\r\n        mov     dword ptr [rsp + 8], 0\r\n        cmp     edi, 2\r\n        je      .LBB2_3\r\n        mov     dword ptr [rsp + 8], 1\r\n        mov     dword ptr [rsp + 12], esi\r\n        cmp     esi, 1\r\n        jne     .LBB2_3\r\n        add     rsp, 104\r\n        ret\r\n\r\n; https://godbolt.org/z/P8T4rboac (best-case)\r\nexample::with_generic_assert:\r\n        sub     rsp, 104\r\n        mov     dword ptr [rsp + 16], 0\r\n        cmp     edi, 2\r\n        je      .LBB2_3\r\n        cmp     esi, 1\r\n        jne     .LBB2_3\r\n        add     rsp, 104\r\n        ret\r\n\r\nexample::without_generic_assert:\r\n        cmp     edi, 2\r\n        je      .LBB3_3\r\n        cmp     esi, 1\r\n        jne     .LBB3_3\r\n        ret\r\n```", "created_at": "2022-04-28T01:07:22Z", "updated_at": "2022-06-15T20:43:13Z", "closed_at": "2022-06-15T20:43:13Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "5ab016c001fb46b087161102119108dd55cf0adf", "assignee": {"login": "oli-obk", "id": 332036, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzMjAzNg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/332036?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk", "html_url": "https://github.com/oli-obk", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com